	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A trademark is a designation of origin. "NES" and "Famicom" are abbreviations of Nintendo's trademarks, so without further qualification, they must refer to Nintendo products.
<br />
<br />Famicom: 60-pin 8-bit game console produced by Nintendo
<br />NES: 72-pin 8-bit game console produced by Nintendo
<br />Famiclone: Any other 60-pin console compatible (to varying extents) with games for Famicom

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


